    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "UNIDENTIFIED FLYING OBJECTS",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "In response to a letter directed by him to Mr.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "Robert Cutler, Special Assistant to President Dwight D.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "Eisenhower, reflecting that he might have some information",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "about the rocket in Texas,\" [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "[REDACTED] Detroit, was interviewed November 7, 1957,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "and furnished the following information:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "Born February 19, 1926 in the State of Warsaw, Poland,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "[REDACTED] was brought from Poland as a prisoner of war to",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "Gut Alt Golssen, approximately 30 miles east of Berlin, Germany,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "in May, 1942, where he remained until a few weeks after the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "end of World War II. He spent the following years at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "Displaced Persons Camps at Work, Strasburg, Offenburg, Wilhelm",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "and Freiburg, Germany. He attended a radio technician school",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "at Freiburg, and for about a year was employed in a textile",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "mill at Laurachbaden, Germany. He arrived in the United",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "States at New York, May 2, 1951, via the \"U.S.S. General Stewart\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "as a displaced person, destined to the Reverend [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "[REDACTED] Hamtramck, Michigan; his alien registration number -",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "[REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "Since May, 1951, he has been employed at the Gobel",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "Brewery, Detroit.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "News report of mysterious vehicle in Texas causing",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "engines to stall prompted him to communicate with the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "United States Government concerning a similar phenomenon",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "observed by him in 1944 in the area of Gut Alt Golssen.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "According to [REDACTED] during",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "1944, month not recalled,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "while enroute to work in a field a short distance north of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "Gut Alt Golssen, their tractor engine stalled on a road through",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "a swamp area. No machinery or other vehicle was then visible",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "although a noise was heard described as a high-pitched whine",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "similar to that produced by a large electric generator.",
      "status": "image_matched"
